I had this problem too. I fixed it by waiting for the 'loadedmetadata' event from the videojs player before showing my video. e.g.

``` javascript
var player = BV.getPlayer();
player.on('loadedmetadata', function(){
    $('#my-video-wrapper').show();
});
```

There's an option to put the video inside a container element when you construct the BigVideo object. For example:

``` javascript
var BV = new $.BigVideo({
    container: $('#my-video-wrapper')
});

BV.getPlayer().on('loadedmetadata', function(){
    $('#my-video-wrapper').show();
});
```

So if "#my-video-wrapper" exists in your document, you can hide it initially using CSS and then the event callback will show it. I haven't got this to work with the BigVideo Flash fallback in Firefox yet though.

